      <h3>What is the campaign?</h3>
      

      The 100 Beds for Haiti Campaign is made up of creative and passionate citizens, students, and professionals dedicated to improving health services in Haiti. 
      <br />
      <br />
      Hundreds of thousands of displaced Haitians have relocated to Northern Haiti to escape the physical devastation of the January earthquake.  As Haiti&#8217;s largest and best functioning private hospital, the H&ocirc;pital Sacr&eacute; Coeur (HSC) currently has 73 permanent inpatient beds and the need for more quality hospital beds is overwhelming.   In partnership with HSC and the Center for the Rural Development of Milot (CRUDEM), we aim to raise $300,000 to purchase and deliver 100 hospital beds to meet this immediate need and support the sustainable, long-term recovery and development of Haiti.
